          <msContents>
            <summary>Psalter, ዳዊት፡ Ff. 1r-122r. Psalter, Dawit, ዳዊት: Ff. 1r–109v: Psalms of David,
              መዝሙር ዘዳዊት; Psalm 77 does not mark the midpoint; Psalm 119 identifies the spiritual
              meaning of the Hebrew letters with the simple modern system; Psalm 151 contains the
              short version; ff. 110r–121r: Biblical Canticles, መሓልየ ነቢያት; ff. 135v–143r: Song of
              Songs, መኃልየ መኃልይ, common version; ff. 143r–151v: Praises of Mary, ውዳሴ ማርያም, arranged
              for the days of the week: Monday (f. 143r), Tuesday (f. 144r), Wednesday (f. 145r),
              Thursday (f. 147r), Friday (f. 148v), Saturday (f. 149v), Sunday (f. 150v); ff.
              151v–154v: Gate of Light, አንቀጸ ብርሃን. </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
              <locus from="1r" to="154v" facs="003">Fols 1r–154v</locus>
              <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
              <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                <locus from="1r" to="122r" facs="003">Fols 1r–122r</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual</span></ref> with the simple
                  modern system</note>
                <note><locus target="#121v">Fol. 121v</locus>, Psalm 151 contains only the first of the four plusses
                  that together constitute the long version</note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                <locus from="122r" to="135v" facs="124">Fols 122r–135v</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
                <note><locus target="#126v">Fol. 126v</locus>
                  <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2257salota#Hannah"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2257salota#Hannah</span></ref>, here identified as <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎተ፡ ሐና፡ ነቢይት፡</foreign>, Prayer of Hana, Prophetess</q></note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                <locus from="135v" to="143r" facs="138">Fols 135v–143r</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">Song of Songs</title>
                <note>common version</note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                <locus from="143r" to="150v" facs="145">Fols 143r–150v</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse
                                                  Māryām</title>
                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.1">
                  <locus from="143r" facs="145">Fols 143r and following</locus>
                  <title>Monday</title>
                </msItem>
                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.2">
                  <locus from="144r" facs="146">Fols 144r and following</locus>
                  <title>Tuesday</title>
                </msItem>
                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.3">
