              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc>picture of Ethiopians gathered for a meal with the following text:
                    <q>“Traditional dinner of fiery stew and barley beer spreads before the author,
                    who was invited to the home of a family in Lalibela, kneeling hostess serves the
                    meal. Musicians play washint and masinko, a flute and one-stringed violin. An
                    isolated village of rock-hewn churches, Lalibela is one of Ethiopia’s holiest
